This guide introduces the migration of Samba3 to Samba4 with LDAP on Gentoo boxes.

== Pre-requisite ==
* A working samba 3 NT PDC (Must be PDC as it will be '''Promote''' to AD)
* Samba AD DNS Planing
* LDAP Auth Backend Database (Optional)


{{Warning| Don't not test migration in your production environment, Once a Windows client finds and connects to the new server, it is not possible to go back! the windows client will never talk to your samba 3 server even if you remove the samba 4 Server...}}

Make sure you thoroughly test your conversion and how your clients react before you activate your new server in your production environment! 



